\title{Ideal observer theory quip}
\tag{joke}

\p{"Ideal observer theory": morality comes from what such an observer (who acquires everyone's preferences and puts them together) would do. However, we don't want this third party to do this in a way that's completely alien to us.
}
\p{Roderick Firth puts it that the observer is "omniscient, disinterested, dispassionate, but otherwise normal".
}